3. Electoral and Other Legislation (Accountability, Integrity and Other Matters) Amendment Act 2020
The Electoral and Other Legislation (Accountability, Integrity and Other Matters) Amendment Act 2020 has introduced new requirements and changes that will impact Councillors and local governments. The changes can be summarised as follows:
· New requirements for register of interests;
· New and clarified requirements for conflicts of interest;
· New requirements for Councillor Advisors and councillor administrative support staff;
· Provisions relating to the dissolution of a local government and administrators;
· Provisions stopping mayors from giving directions about the appointment or discipline of local government employees; and
· Changes for filling Councillor and Mayoral vacancies.
